    <!-- About -->
    <sys:String x:Key="Text_AboutProgram">
        Windows Customize Wizard Beta\n
        \n
        Windows Customize Wizard is a utility for working with Windows images\n
        and servicing the local operating system environment.\n
        \n
        The application allows mounting and processing WIM/ESD images,\n
        managing Windows components, features, Appx packages, drivers,\n
        and performing cleanup and optimization operations.\n
        \n
        Main features:\n
        • WIM/ESD image management\n
        • Local system servicing\n
        • Component and feature management\n
        • Appx package management\n
        • Driver collection and integration\n
        • Image cleanup and integrity checks\n
        • DISM-based processing tools\n
        \n
        The program is intended for advanced users, testers,\n
        system administrators, and Windows customization enthusiasts.\n
        \n
        Developer: ZaKadrom\n
        © 2026 ZaKadrom
    </sys:String>
    <!-- End -->

    <!-- Help -->
    <sys:String x:Key="Text_HelpProgram">
        Windows Customize Wizard Help\n
        \n
        Quick start:\n
        \n
        1. Select a Windows ISO image.\n
        2. Mount the required WIM/ESD index.\n
        3. Open Features, Packages, or Appx sections.\n
        4. Enable, disable, or remove components.\n
        5. Save changes to the mounted image.\n
        6. Unmount the image after completion.\n
        \n
        Available tools:\n
        • Mount and unmount Windows images\n
        • Local system servicing\n
        • Component management\n
        • Appx package control\n
        • Driver export and integration\n
        • Image cleanup and optimization\n
        • Image integrity verification\n
        • Conversion between WIM and ESD\n
        \n
        Important:\n
        • Run the application as Administrator.\n
        • Do not close the program during image servicing.\n
        • Large images may require significant disk space.\n
        • DISM operations can take a long time depending on image size.\n
        \n
        Developer: ZaKadrom\n
        © 2026 ZaKadrom
    </sys:String>
